data.name: ToolTipCapacitorESeries
data.value: Specifies the preferred E series for capacitors.

data.name: ToolTipConverterName
data.value: The text field of 16 characters - for annotation purposes only.

data.name: ToolTipDesiredVoutRipple
data.value: The maximum allowable ripple that appears on the output of the voltage regulator. The ripple effect comes from the RC circuit designed to trim/margin the converter.

data.name: ToolTipMarginHighPercent
data.value: The desired converter output voltage in response to a margin high request in % of the nominal voltage.

data.name: ToolTipMarginHighV
data.value: The desired converter output voltage in response to a margin high request in volts.

data.name: ToolTipMarginLowPercent
data.value: The desired converter output voltage in response to a margin low request in % of the nominal voltage.

data.name: ToolTipMarginLowV
data.value: The desired converter output voltage in response to a margin low request in volts.

data.name: ToolTipMaxVoltage
data.value: The maximum converter output voltage.

data.name: ToolTipMinVoltage
data.value: The minimum converter output voltage.

data.name: ToolTipMinVoltageActual
data.value: The calculated minimum voltage based on actual values of the external RC circuit.

data.name: ToolTipNominalVadjOutput
data.value: The control voltage at the Adjust/Feedback control pin to achieve the nominal output voltage.

data.name: ToolTipNominalVoltage
data.value: The nominal converter output voltage.

data.name: ToolTipR1
data.value: The external scaling resistor value (in kΩ) required to achieve the correct voltage on the Adjust/Feedback control pin to achieve the nominal output voltage when the PWM output is disabled.

data.name: ToolTipR2
data.value: The external scaling resistor value (in kΩ) required to achieve the correct voltage on the Adjust/Feedback control pin to achieve the nominal output voltage when the PWM output is disabled.

data.name: ToolTipR2Calc
data.value: The ideal calculated value for R2.

data.name: ToolTipR3
data.value: The external resistor value used on the PCB to calculate the actual dynamic range.

data.name: ToolTipR3plusR4Actual
data.value: The sum of the actual resistance values for R3 and R4.

data.name: ToolTipR3plusR4Calc
data.value: The sum of the calculated resistance values chosen in the customizer for R3 and R4.

data.name: ToolTipR4
data.value: The external resistor value used on the PCB to calculate the actual ripple.

data.name: ToolTipResistorsESeries
data.value: Specifies the preferred E series for resistors.

data.name: ToolTipStartupVoltage
data.value: The user configurable startup voltage for the converter.

data.name: ToolTipVohOfPwmOutput
data.value: The output voltage to use with the associated PWM output pin.

data.name: ToolTipVoutRippleActual
data.value: The maximum allowable ripple that appears on the output of the voltage regulator. The ripple effect comes from the RC circuit designed to trim/margin the converter.
